  34.6.6 ESMF_XGridIsCreated - Check whether a XGrid object has been created

   INTERFACE:
   function ESMF_XGridIsCreated(xgrid, rc)

   RETURN VALUE:
     logical :: ESMF_XGridIsCreated

   ARGUMENTS:
     type(ESMF_XGrid), intent(in)            :: xgrid
 -- The following arguments require argument keyword syntax (e.g. rc=rc). --
     integer,             intent(out), optional :: rc

   DESCRIPTION:

   Return .true. if the xgrid has been created. Otherwise return .false..
   If an error occurs, i.e. rc /= ESMF_SUCCESS is returned, the return
   value of the function will also be .false..

   The arguments are:

   xgrid
          ESMF_XGrid queried.

   [rc]
          Return code; equals ESMF_SUCCESS if there are no errors.

